250 g Salmon Fillets, skin-on
1 tbsp Enchilada Spice Blend
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 unit(s) Lime
7 g Cilantro
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
43 mL Creamy Dressing
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
113 g Corn Kernels
½ tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Sprinkle corn over baking sheet, then set aside.
Pat salmon dry with paper towels, then season with Enchilada Spice Blend, salt and pepper.
Place salmon on top of corn, skin-side down, on the prepared baking sheet. Roast in the middle of the oven until golden-brown and cooked through, 8-12 min.**

Meanwhile, zest lime. Juice lime into a large bowl.
Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil and 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar to the bowl with lime juice. Whisk to combine.
Add coleslaw mix to bowl, then toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.
In a small bowl, add lime zest, creamy dressing and mayo. Stir to combine.

Break up each salmon fillet into 6 equal pieces.
Lay out tortillas on a clean surface. (TIP: Wrap tortillas in paper towels. Microwave until tortillas are warm and flexible, 30 sec-1 min.)

Divide slaw, corn and salmon between tortillas. (TIP: Remove skin, if desired!)
Tear and sprinkle cilantro over top of filling.
Drizzle with Baja sauce, then sprinkle feta over top.
Divide tacos between plates.

If you've opted to get salmon, roast in the same way the recipe instructs you to roast tilapia, then decrease the roast time to 8-10 min.**